  "prompt": "Why are Pug/Cavalier mix puppies so expensive?",
  "response": "Pug/Cavalier King Charles Spaniel mix puppies (often called \"Pugaliers\") can be expensive for several reasons:\n\n1. Designer breed popularity\n- Relatively new and trendy mixed breed\n- Perceived as cute and unique\n\n2. Low breeding frequency\n- Not as common as purebred dogs\n- Fewer breeders specializing in this mix\n\n3. Potential health costs\n- Both parent breeds have known health issues\n- Breeding requires careful genetic screening\n- Higher veterinary care during breeding process\n\n4. Demand\n- Increasing interest in hybrid/designer dogs\n- Compact size appealing to urban pet owners\n\n5. Breeding challenges\n- Careful selection of parent dogs\n- Potential need for artificial insemination\n- Small litter sizes\n\n6. Individual breeder factors\n- Reputation of the breeder\n- Quality of parent dogs\n- Included initial veterinary care\n\nPrices can range from $1,000 to $3,000 depending on location, breeder reputation, and specific puppy characteristics. However, potential owners should be aware of potential inherited health issues from both parent breeds and consider adoption as an alternative.",
